description:
Since his childhood, Ahmed has shown strong passion about the IT/security fields as he started using several hacking techniques at an early age. After succeeding in combining the mathematics, the algorithms, the time and stress management techniques, and the versatility he acquired from his studies in the preparatory classes for engineering schools, he was able to graduate as a state engineer from the National School of Computer Science and Systems Analysis in Rabat in 2015.

Throughout his career, he managed to build an expert profile in the fields information systems and management skills, infrastructure, organization and security, and has also obtained multiple certifications : ISO 27001Lead Auditor, ISO 27005 Lead Risk manager,  CEHv8, CEHv9, Certified Application Security Analyst...

As a first step in his career, he began in the marketing and digital development Sector, then moved to Security and Investigation Sector. On the side,he enjoyed his work as a freelancer in multiple projects in Pentesting, Risk analysis, Security policy development, Deployment of security solutions and forensics.

For over 6 years of experience, Ahmed developed a broad view and diverse skills in IT at organizational, tactical (ISO 27001, ITIL, COBIT, security Policy, PMO, ,Datacenter, Technical Architectures) and operational (management teams, dashboards, infrastructure Management SLA, incident Management, Supervision, technical migration, PenTesting, configuration review, ...) levels. This variety of knowledge allows Ahmed to be aware of the issues, the challenges, and the expectations of companies and organizations in the field.
